上周，《模拟人生4&#34；我的婚礼故事&#34；包括高度关注同性婚姻的扩展包表示，扩展不会&#39；不会在俄罗斯发行，在那里&#34；由于联邦法律，我们的故事情节可能会发生变化&#34; 现在，电子游戏公司EA已经推翻了这一决定，称这一扩展实际上将在俄罗斯发布&#34；未更改和未更改#34；与世界其他地方并驾齐驱。在周三下午发布在电子艺术网站上的最新消息中，模拟人生团队写道，他们之前认为&#34；我们的团队无法自由分享俄罗斯同性伴侣Cam和Dom的故事&#34; 那&#39；这显然是对俄罗斯的间接提及#39；s第6.13.1条法律禁止&#34；未成年人中的宣传或同性恋&#34; 根据这条法律，团队决定&#34；要坚持我们分享他们故事的承诺，最好的办法就是不在俄罗斯发布这个包&#34;
现在，这场比赛的幕后团队表示他们已经&#34；重新评估了我们的选择，并意识到我们可以做的比我们最初认为的更多&#34; 34岁；我的婚礼故事&#34；pack将于2月23日在俄罗斯和世界其他地方发射，比原定的2月17日发射日期推迟了几天。
在最新消息中，模拟人生团队提到了&#34；来自我们社区的情感流露，包括对我们决定的支持和对社区其他成员的关心&#34; 那&#39；这在一定程度上明显是指#俄罗斯婚礼运动。最近几天，该运动在社交媒体上充斥着敦促电子艺术改变决定的信息，并最终在俄罗斯发布该组合。
SimplyHao在这篇冗长的推特帖子中总结了这场运动的主旨。SimplyHao认为俄罗斯&#39；第39条；只要标有&#34，就不会影响游戏；18+&#34; 年龄分级和面向成年人的营销，这就是模拟人生4过去在俄罗斯的营销方式&#34;最近所有审查和削减的案例都与自我审查有关，因为担心遭到抵制，&#34；SimplyHao写道，&#34；不是关于俄罗斯政府的一些要求。这就是EA本身所做的自我审查&#34;
许多请愿书提出了类似的观点，认为&#34；游戏的取消只会使俄罗斯同性伴侣的权利状况恶化。通过取消婚礼故事包，你接受了他们的同性恋恐惧游戏规则&#34;
&#34;爱就是爱，对于那些希望看到一个人人都是如此的世界的人来说，模拟人生社区将继续是一个安全的空间；EA团队在《今日》中写道&#39；更新&#34;我们感谢团队的支持和我们的价值观，即使在困难的时候。谢谢你成为模拟人生的一部分&#34;

note_en:
Last week, the team behind  The Sims 4 &#34;My Wedding Stories&#34; expansion pack—which includes  a heavy focus on same-sex marriages—said that the expansion  wouldn&#39;t be released in Russia where &#34;our storytelling would be subject to changes because of federal laws.&#34; Now, video game company EA has reversed that decision, saying the expansion will in fact be released in Russia &#34;unaltered and unchanged&#34; alongside the rest of the world. In  an update posted Wednesday afternoon on the Electronic Arts website,  The Sims team writes that it previously believed that &#34;our team could not freely share the storytelling of same-sex couple Cam and Dom in Russia.&#34; That&#39;s an apparent oblique reference to  Russia&#39;s Article 6.13.1 law, which prohibits &#34;propaganda or homosexualism among minors.&#34; Given that law, the team had decided that &#34;the best way to uphold our commitment to sharing their story was to not release this pack [in Russia].&#34;
 Now, the team behind the game says it has &#34;reassessed our options and realized we can do more than we initially believed...&#34; The &#34;My Wedding Stories&#34; pack will now launch in Russia and the rest of the world on February 23, a delay of a few days from its original planned launch date of February 17.
     In its latest message,  The Sims team makes reference to &#34;the outpouring of feelings from our community including both support for our decision and concern for their fellow community members.&#34; That&#39;s in part an apparent reference to  the #WeddingsForRussia campaign, which in recent days has flooded social media with messages urging Electronic Arts to reverse its decision and release the pack in Russia after all.
 The main thrust of that campaign is summed up in  this lengthy Twitter thread by SimplyHao. SimplyHao argued that Russia&#39;s laws wouldn&#39;t actually affect the game as long as it was labeled with an &#34;18+&#34; age rating and marketed to adults, which is how  The Sims 4  has been marketed in Russia in the past. &#34;All the recent cases of censorship and cuts were about self-censorship in fear of backlash,&#34; SimplyHao writes, &#34;not about some demand of the Russian government. And this is what EA does—just self-censors itself.&#34;
  A  number of  petitions made similar points, arguing that &#34;cancellation of the game can only worsen the situation with the rights of same-sex couples in Russia. By canceling The Wedding Stories Pack you accepted their homophobic rules of the game.&#34;
 &#34;Love is love, and  The Sims community will continue to be a safe space for those who want to see a world where that is true for everyone,&#34; the EA team writes in today&#39;s update. &#34;We are thankful for the support of our team and our values even when it is hard. Thank you for being a part of  The Sims.&#34;
